com.ibm.team.repository.client.util
Class RepositoryUtil

java.lang.Object
  com.ibm.team.repository.client.util.RepositoryUtil

public class RepositoryUtil
extends java.lang.Object

Utilities for retrieving information given a specified repository. The information returned requires no authorization or special protocol (and thus is limited in what is available).

getRepositoryId

public static UUID getRepositoryId(java.lang.String repositoryURI)
Returns the UUID of the repository identified by repositoryURI. The repository is contacted.

IMPORTANT NOTE: This routine is not cancellable.

Parameters:
repositoryURI - The URI to the repository. Must not be null.
Returns:
The UUID of the specified repository. null if the repository could not be contacted, or if an error occurred.

getRepositoryTime

public static java.sql.Timestamp getRepositoryTime(ITeamRepository repo,
                                                   org.eclipse.core.runtime.IProgressMonitor monitor)
                                            throws TeamRepositoryException
Returns the time of the server identified by repo. The repository is contacted.

Parameters:
repo - The repository to contact. Must not be null.
monitor - The progress monitor. May be null.
Returns:
